				First off, I've got a hunch that's getting stronger and stronger,=
 that Sven isn't the one perpetrating this=2E  If he was, he=
 would've definitely locked his screen the previous night while=
 he was uploading=2E  He knew that there were people looking into=
 the case, so if he was actually the perpetrator, he would've=
 covered his tracks at least a little bit=2E  

I'm not quite convinced that the person who's doing it is=
 necessarily trying to frame Sven, though=2E  If they were, I don't=
 think they would've reset the preferences either the previous=
 night or that morning=2E  

I'm trying to figure out who *is* doing this, though=2E  I'm pretty=
 sure it's an insider, and I'm thinking it's probably someone who=
 knows Sven's schedule reasonably well=2E  Kurt could do it, but if=
 it was him, he wouldn't've needed to set Sven's screen to not=
 lock automatically=2E  

As for why the only directory being shared was C:\STUFF, I'd say=
 that the person who is doing this is someone who stays at work=
 an hour or so later than Sven=2E  When Sven leaves, on specific=
 days, they go and add the other directories to limewire, starts=
 limewire sharing, waits an hour or so, then removes the=
 directories again=2E=2E=2E  They have a contact at GB who knows the=
 days and times that the files will be shared, who goes and grabs=
 what they want, looks through, and decides what to post=2E

If I were investigating this, I'd probably want to do something=
 with the really cool little cameras that you've used in other=
 cases=2E  Probably, I'd just set them up to record starting a bit=
 before Sven leaves for the day, until the P2P traffic starts up=
 again=2E  (or until it stops?)=2E  Another option would be to set up=
 the cameras, and then wait for the transfer's to start, then=
 record until the next morning, and see who pulled the shared=
 directories off again=2E

The big question is who would you speak to about permission for=
 setting up the cameras=2E  Definitely, I wouldn't tell Sven, Kurt,=
 or most other people=2E=2E=2E  Maybe just talk to the CEO or whoever=
 it was that pulled you in?  I really don't trust Kurt ---=
 something tells me he's involved, even though I have given=
 reasons for why it's probably not him actually doing this=2E  

Chief, you've really got me completely addicted=2E=2E=2E  I keep=
 catching myself thinking about these cases and what the next=
 step is going to be!  Thanks for addicting me!  

~TuxGirl

